class.description:
[PckDumper] extracts the raw files stored inside a Godot PCK archive to disk. Unlike [ImportExporter], it does not convert resources back to their source formats - it writes exactly the bytes that are stored in the archive. Use it when you need the engine-format files (e.g. [code].ctex[/code] instead of [code].png[/code], [code].gdc[/code] instead of [code].gd[/code]) rather than their original source equivalents.
Load a project with [method GDRESettings.load_project] before using [PckDumper].
[codeblock]
var settings = Engine.get_singleton("GDRESettings")
var err = settings.load_project(PackedStringArray(["path/to/game.pck"]))
if err != OK:
    push_error("Failed to load project: " + str(err))
    return

var dumper = PckDumper.new()
err = dumper.check_md5_all_files()
if err != OK and err != ERR_SKIP:
    push_warning("Checksum verification failed - archive may be corrupt")

err = dumper.pck_dump_to_dir("/path/to/output")
if err != OK:
    push_error("Extraction failed: " + str(err))

settings.unload_project()
[/codeblock]
